<span id="freeTextContainer2501006182833443930">I admittedly liked the first one a little more, but this series has caught me by surprise by sparking my interest in historical LDS events when before it used to be like a modern Old Testament to me through its confusing turn of events and many moving parts. It looks like the power of fiction wins out again for me because I have enjoyed it a good deal more through the eyes of a main cast of fictional characters. Some aspects are a little too cheesy for me by clearly seeking out emotional respons</span>
  <span id="freeText2501006182833443930" style="display:none">I admittedly liked the first one a little more, but this series has caught me by surprise by sparking my interest in historical LDS events when before it used to be like a modern Old Testament to me through its confusing turn of events and many moving parts. It looks like the power of fiction wins out again for me because I have enjoyed it a good deal more through the eyes of a main cast of fictional characters. Some aspects are a little too cheesy for me by clearly seeking out emotional responses from the readers, but I enjoy what I've gleaned about this focus of history so far.</span>
